      "content": "Feeling weak on one side along with a severe headache and facial changes *is* more than just a typical migraine aura; that's a significant red flag. While migraines are common, weakness needs to be addressed by a doctor immediately because it can point to other issues. For this level of intensity and neurological change, going to the ER is the wisest move to rule out anything more serious and get the right treatment fast.",
